      *> DFHRESP  EXEC CICS EIBRESP condition codes.
      *>
      *> COPY DFHRESP into WORKING-STORAGE SECTION, then compare
      *> EIBRESP against named codes instead of bare integers:
      *>
      *>     EVALUATE EIBRESP
      *>         WHEN RESP-NORMAL      ...    *> bricks mnemonic
      *>         WHEN DFHRESP-NORMAL   ...    *> classic CICS alias
      *>         WHEN RESP-NOTFND      ...
      *>     END-EVALUATE.
      *>
      *> Every code is declared twice -- once under the bricks-style
      *> RESP-* mnemonic and once under the IBM-traditional
      *> DFHRESP-* alias.  Both forms resolve to the same numeric
      *> value, so programs may pick either style or mix them.
      *>
      *> The numeric values match cics/resp.go in the bricks
      *> runtime; if a new condition is added there, mirror it
      *> here so user programs can name it.
       01 RESP-NORMAL       PIC S9(8) VALUE 0.
       01 DFHRESP-NORMAL    PIC S9(8) VALUE 0.
       01 RESP-ERROR        PIC S9(8) VALUE 1.
       01 DFHRESP-ERROR     PIC S9(8) VALUE 1.
       01 RESP-EOC          PIC S9(8) VALUE 6.
       01 DFHRESP-EOC       PIC S9(8) VALUE 6.
       01 RESP-NOTFND       PIC S9(8) VALUE 13.
       01 DFHRESP-NOTFND    PIC S9(8) VALUE 13.
       01 RESP-DUPREC       PIC S9(8) VALUE 14.
       01 DFHRESP-DUPREC    PIC S9(8) VALUE 14.
       01 RESP-DUPKEY       PIC S9(8) VALUE 15.
       01 DFHRESP-DUPKEY    PIC S9(8) VALUE 15.
       01 RESP-INVREQ       PIC S9(8) VALUE 16.
       01 DFHRESP-INVREQ    PIC S9(8) VALUE 16.
       01 RESP-IOERR        PIC S9(8) VALUE 17.
       01 DFHRESP-IOERR     PIC S9(8) VALUE 17.
       01 RESP-NOSPACE      PIC S9(8) VALUE 18.
       01 DFHRESP-NOSPACE   PIC S9(8) VALUE 18.
       01 RESP-NOTOPEN      PIC S9(8) VALUE 19.
       01 DFHRESP-NOTOPEN   PIC S9(8) VALUE 19.
       01 RESP-ENDFILE      PIC S9(8) VALUE 20.
       01 DFHRESP-ENDFILE   PIC S9(8) VALUE 20.
       01 RESP-ILLOGIC      PIC S9(8) VALUE 21.
       01 DFHRESP-ILLOGIC   PIC S9(8) VALUE 21.
       01 RESP-LENGERR      PIC S9(8) VALUE 22.
